  <static seed="1193" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/divideRationalExpressions25.pg">
    <statement><p>Simplify this expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{({2x-4}) \div ({8x-16}) =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{1}{4}, x\ne -\left(-2\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   ({2x-4}) \div ({8x-16}) 
      \amp = \frac{{2x-4}}{1} \div \frac{{8x-16}}{1} \\
      \amp = \frac{{2x-4}}{1} \cdot {\frac{1}{8x-16}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{2\mathopen{}\left(x-2\right)}}{1} \cdot \frac{1}{{8\mathopen{}\left(x-2\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{1}{4}, x\ne -\left(-2\right)}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>x - 2</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification are <m>x \ne {2}</m>.</p>
</solution>
